  3. User Pre and Post Processing

     The User Pre Processing Script and Post Processing Script are files used
     to execute tasks when the user time starts and when the user time finishes.
  
     The path of these files are:
       $HOME/.crono/<cluster>.upreps  (Pre Processing)
       $HOME/.crono/<cluster>.upostps (Post Processing)

     When the user time starts, the tasks in the script of Pre Processing
     can be executed until the user time finishes.
     There are some variables available to make the scripts:
         - CR_CLUSTER    = cluster name
         - CR_USERID     = user id
         - CR_USERNAME   = user name
         - CR_NODES      = list of user nodes (e.g. : "tropical01 tropical02")
         - CR_NODESINFO  = list of user nodes with additional information
              Format: (for each node)
                 <hostname>:<nodetype>:<architecture>:
                 <number of processes>:"<description>"<space>
         - CR_RID       = request id

      The upreps and upostps can be either scripts or programs.

  3.1 UPREPS and Batch jobs

     -  Both of them use a script that is executed when the user time starts.
     -  You can use the UPREPS and Batch Jobs together.
     -  When the execution of a batch jobs script finishes the user time
        also finishes.
     -  When the execution of a UPREPS finishes the user time doesn't finish.
        For example, if a user requested 5 minutes and the UPREPS is executed 
        in 1 minute, the user still has 4 minutes (in interactive mode).

