  4. Example of a session using the CRONO commands 


  1) Let's start using the crsetdef command to setup the some values of the
     unspecified parameters:

     $ crsetdef cluster cluster1
     $ crsetdef time 15
     $ crsetdef nodes 14
     $ crsetdef mpirun mpiether
     $ crsetdef mpicomp mpiethercc
     $ crsetdef arch ia32

  2) To view who is using the cluster cluster1 type:
     $ crqview

  3) You can view the users of another cluster, for example:
     $ crqview -c cluster2

  4) To get some resources use the cralloc command:
     $ cralloc
  
  5) If you want for example sixteen nodes type:
     $ cralloc -n 16
     Or
     $ crsetdef nodes 16
     $ cralloc

  6) To compile a hello.c program using the mpi ethernet use the crcomp script:
     $ crcomp hello.c -o hello
     You can execute
     $ crcomp -env mpiethercc hello.c -o hello
 
     But the -env options is not necessary because the crsetdef was used to
     define the mpicomp.
   
  7) To run the hello using twelve processes you can use the crrun script:
     $ crrun hello -np 12


